                                                <xs:enumeration value="Public listed company, majority owned subsidiary or related entity of a public listed company; government entity, international organisation, central bank, or wholly owned subsidiary of a government entity, international organisation, or central bank" />
                                                <xs:enumeration value="New Zealand registered charity or deceased estate" />
                                                <xs:enumeration value="Passive non-financial entity (NFE)">
                                                  <xs:annotation>
                                                    <xs:documentation source="note">A passive NFE applies when 50% or more of its total gross income for the preceding year was passive income and/or 50% or more of assets held for the preceding year produced that passive income.  
Passive income is generally income that is not derived from the conduct of an active business activity.  Examples of passive income are: income primarily generated from investment sources such as interest, dividends and rent collected.
A passive NFE is not a financial institution.</xs:documentation>
                                                  </xs:annotation>
